---
import HowItWorksOverlays from './HowItWorksOverlays.astro';
---

<section id="how-it-works" aria-labelledby="how-it-works-heading" class="bg-[#262626] py-20 md:py-28 relative overflow-hidden">
  <!-- Section glow accent -->
  <div class="section-glow absolute -top-24 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[min(800px,90vw)] h-[300px] blur-[64px] opacity-[0.15] md:opacity-[0.20] pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
    <h2 id="how-it-works-heading" class="text-white font-extrabold text-2xl md:text-4xl tracking-[-0.02em] mb-10 text-center">
      What Is Flock Safety?
    </h2>

    <!-- Split layout: intro text + divider + carousel -->
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[1fr_1px_1fr] gap-10 md:gap-12 mb-14">
      <!-- Left: intro paragraphs -->
      <div class="space-y-6 text-[#d4d4d4] text-base leading-relaxed min-w-0">
        <p>
          Flock Safety puts cameras on poles at intersections and along roadsides. Small. Solar-powered. Easy to miss. Every car that drives by gets photographed. Your plate number, vehicle make, color, and location get uploaded to Flock's servers automatically. Every time.
        </p>
        <p>
          Here's what your police department may not have mentioned: that data doesn't stay in Greenville. Flock runs a national network. Police from other states can search it. So can federal agencies. Every drive you've taken is in there.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your local police can't turn off the federal access.<br /><span class="text-[#ef4444] font-semibold">And neither can you.</span>
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Vertical divider -->
      <div class="hidden md:block bg-[#404040]"></div>

      <!-- Right: carousel -->
      <div class="factoid-carousel min-w-0" id="factoidCarousel" role="region" aria-label="Case studies carousel">
        <div class="carousel-container">
          <!-- Prev arrow -->
          <button class="carousel-arrow carousel-arrow-prev" id="prevBtn" aria-label="Previous factoid">&lsaquo;</button>

          <!-- Viewport -->
          <div class="carousel-viewport" aria-live="polite">
            <div class="carousel-track" id="carouselTrack">
              <div class="carousel-card" data-idx="0" data-overlay="0" tabindex="0" role="group" aria-label="Case study 1 of 5">
                <div class="carousel-card-content">
                  <span class="block text-[#ef4444] font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.05em] mb-3">Greenville, SC &mdash; False Arrest</span>
                  <p class="text-[#d4d4d4] text-[0.9rem] leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    Two sisters driving a rental car were flagged as stolen by a Flock camera. Police drew weapons and handcuffed both women. The car wasn't stolen &mdash; it had been improperly reported. They are now suing Greenville PD.
                  </p>
                  <span class="read-more-text">See the full lawsuit story &rarr;</span>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="carousel-card" data-idx="1" data-overlay="1" tabindex="-1" role="group" aria-label="Case study 2 of 5">
                <div class="carousel-card-content">
                  <span class="block text-[#ef4444] font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.05em] mb-3">Data Retention &mdash; 3 Years, Not 30 Days</span>
                  <p class="text-[#d4d4d4] text-[0.9rem] leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    Flock claims 30-day deletion. But Greenville's data goes to SLED, which keeps it for three years. When a reporter asked SLED for misconduct records, they refused to answer.
                  </p>
                  <span class="read-more-text">See what SLED won't disclose &rarr;</span>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="carousel-card" data-idx="2" data-overlay="2" tabindex="-1" role="group" aria-label="Case study 3 of 5">
                <div class="carousel-card-content">
                  <span class="block text-[#ef4444] font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.05em] mb-3">Santa Cruz, CA &mdash; 4,000 Federal Searches</span>
                  <p class="text-[#d4d4d4] text-[0.9rem] leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    State agencies accessed local camera data 4,000 times on behalf of federal authorities &mdash; including ICE &mdash; before the city found out and cancelled the contract 6&ndash;1.
                  </p>
                  <span class="read-more-text">See why the city voted 6&ndash;1 to cancel &rarr;</span>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="carousel-card" data-idx="3" data-overlay="3" tabindex="-1" role="group" aria-label="Case study 4 of 5">
                <div class="carousel-card-content">
                  <span class="block text-[#ef4444] font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.05em] mb-3">Spartanburg, SC &mdash; Sheriff Convicted</span>
                  <p class="text-[#d4d4d4] text-[0.9rem] leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    Spartanburg County Sheriff Chuck Wright oversaw Flock deployments and pled guilty to federal charges: conspiracy to commit theft and wire fraud. The man with access to your location history was a convicted federal criminal.
                  </p>
                  <span class="read-more-text">See who had access to your data &rarr;</span>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="carousel-card" data-idx="4" data-overlay="4" tabindex="-1" role="group" aria-label="Case study 5 of 5">
                <div class="carousel-card-content">
                  <span class="block text-[#ef4444] font-bold text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.05em] mb-3">Austin, TX &mdash; No Crime Reduction</span>
                  <p class="text-[#d4d4d4] text-[0.9rem] leading-relaxed mb-4">
                    Austin's own city audit couldn't find evidence the cameras reduce crime. Over 20% of searches lacked proper documentation. The city cancelled the contract.
                  </p>
                  <span class="read-more-text">See the audit that killed the contract &rarr;</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Next arrow -->
          <button class="carousel-arrow carousel-arrow-next" id="nextBtn" aria-label="Next factoid">&rsaquo;</button>

          <!-- Dots inside the card area -->
          <div class="carousel-dots-bar" id="carouselDots" role="tablist"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <hr class="border-[#404040] mb-14" />

    <!-- Pull quote -->
    <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-[#ef4444] pl-6 py-4 mb-10">
      <p class="text-[#fafafa] font-bold italic text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed">
        "Your data is shared with agencies you don't control."
      </p>
    </blockquote>

    <p class="text-[#d4d4d4] text-base leading-relaxed">
      These cameras track everyone. Most of the people they photograph have done nothing wrong. All of them end up in the same database.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<HowItWorksOverlays />

<style>
  /* Carousel container -- holds arrows, viewport, and dots as one unit */
  .carousel-container {
    position: relative;
    background: #171717;
    border-radius: 10px;
    padding: 24px 20px 48px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .carousel-container {
      padding: 24px 48px 48px;
    }
  }

  /* Carousel viewport & track */
  .carousel-viewport {
    overflow: hidden;
    width: 100%;
  }
  .carousel-track {
    display: flex;
    width: 100%;
    transition: transform 0.45s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
  }

  /* Carousel cards */
  .carousel-card {
    flex: 0 0 100%;
    min-width: 100%;
    height: 220px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    cursor: pointer;
  }
  .carousel-card-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: space-between;
    height: 100%;
  }
  .carousel-card:hover .read-more-text {
    color: #fcd34d;
  }

  /* Read More text link */
  .read-more-text {
    color: #fbbf24;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  /* Carousel arrows -- integrated into the card */
  .carousel-arrow {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    background: none;
    border: none;
    color: #525252;
    width: 36px;
    height: 36px;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 24px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    transition: color 0.2s;
    line-height: 1;
    z-index: 2;
  }
  .carousel-arrow:hover {
    color: #a3a3a3;
  }
  .carousel-arrow-prev {
    left: 2px;
  }
  .carousel-arrow-next {
    right: 2px;
  }
  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .carousel-arrow-prev {
      left: 8px;
    }
    .carousel-arrow-next {
      right: 8px;
    }
  }

  /* Dots -- bottom of the card */
  .carousel-dots-bar {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 16px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
  }
  :global(.carousel-dot) {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #737373;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.2s;
    border: none;
    padding: 0;
  }
  :global(.carousel-dot.active) {
    background: #ef4444;
  }
</style>

<script>
  import '../scripts/carousel';
</script>
